<paragraph blockId="19.[189,773,1316,1345]" box="[189,773,1316,1345]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,773,1316,1345]" fontSize="12" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="0">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,773,1316,1345]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Notes on genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desv. (Desvaux" authorityYear="1827" box="[400,612,1316,1345]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Didymoglossum</taxonomicName>
in Comoros
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,1368,1817]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName box="[189,483,1368,1394]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lorencei">
<emphasis box="[189,483,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Didymoglossum lorencei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[499,657,1368,1394]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis box="[499,657,1368,1394]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[718,841,1369,1394]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis box="[718,841,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are new for the archipelago. They were never reported, likely due to confusions with morphologically close taxa. We can, however, note here that 
<taxonomicName box="[189,314,1439,1464]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis box="[189,314,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, absent in the archipelago according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Tardieu-Blot M. - L." box="[810,1049,1438,1465]" editor="Humbert H." journalOrPublisher="famille" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="16 - 38" part="3" refString="Tardieu-Blot M. - L. 1951. Hymenophyllacees. In: Humbert H. (ed.) Flore de Madagascar et des Comores, famille 3: 16 - 38. MNHN, Paris." title="Hymenophyllacees" type="journal article" volumeTitle="Flore de Madagascar et des Comores" year="1951">Tardieu-Blot (1951)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Roux J. P." box="[1114,1269,1439,1465]" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" part="23" refString="Roux J. P. 2009. Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands. Strelitzia 23." title="Synopsis of the Lycopodiophyta and Pteridophyta of Africa, Madagascar and neighbouring islands" type="journal volume" year="2009">Roux (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, would be nevertheless present according to the type of 
<taxonomicName box="[703,1122,1474,1500]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="erosum" variety="laciniatum">
<emphasis box="[703,944,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Trichomanes erosum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[997,1122,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">laciniatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which would have been collected in Comoros. But this type specimen could not be observed nor studied, and its identification remains questionable. Sterile 
<taxonomicName box="[534,654,1545,1570]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis box="[534,654,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also indeed easily confused with small sterile 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1391,1544,1570]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[1221,1391,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The confusion is also easy between 
<taxonomicName box="[645,846,1579,1605]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolium">
<emphasis box="[645,846,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. rotundifolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and small 
<taxonomicName box="[992,1118,1580,1605]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Trichomanes" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erosum">
<emphasis box="[992,1118,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. erosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens with entire laminae. The first species never displays lobed fronds contrary to the second. 
<taxonomicName box="[1106,1398,1614,1640]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lorencei">
<emphasis box="[1106,1398,1614,1640]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Didymoglossum lorencei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[243,403,1650,1676]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="robinsonii">
<emphasis box="[243,403,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. robinsonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are often found growing as epiphyte and mixed and confused with other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Desv. (Desvaux" authorityYear="1827" box="[222,411,1685,1711]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[222,411,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Didymoglossum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Only microscopic observation of marginal hairs allows the distinction. It explains that the occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authority="in La" authorityName="in La" box="[457,661,1720,1747]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lorencei">
<emphasis box="[457,590,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. lorencei</emphasis>
in La
</taxonomicName>
Réunion has been reported only recently, because the species is quite discrete and mostly grows on tree-fern trunks in association with the much more abundant 
<taxonomicName box="[189,360,1790,1816]" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Hymenophyllaceae" genus="Didymoglossum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hymenophyllales" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidatum">
<emphasis box="[189,360,1790,1816]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">D. cuspidatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(pers. obs.; 
<bibRefCitation author="Grangaud E." box="[504,691,1790,1817]" journalOrPublisher="MNHN, Paris &amp; Biotope, Meze" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" refString="Grangaud E. 2010. Guide des Fougeres et plantes alliees des Mascareignes. MNHN, Paris &amp; Biotope, Meze." title="Guide des Fougeres et plantes alliees des Mascareignes" type="book" year="2010">Grangaud 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
